See also: toth and Tóth

English

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

From Hungarian Tóth (“Slav”).

Proper noun

[edit]

Toth (plural Toths)

A surname from Hungarian.

Statistics

[edit]

According to the 2010 United States Census, Toth is the 1826th most common surname in the United States, belonging to 19606 individuals. Toth is most common among White (95.78%) individuals.

Further reading

[edit]

Hanks, Patrick, editor (2003), “Toth”, in Dictionary of American Family Names, volume 3, New York City: Oxford University Press, →ISBN.

Anagrams

[edit]
